                            <comment id="121482" author="jamesanunez" created="Thu, 16 Jul 2015 20:10:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can close this ticket since &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6661&quot; title=&quot;Interop DNE2 test between DNE2 clients and 2.5/2.7 servers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6661&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6661&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; takes care of this case and more.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="116694" author="gerrit" created="Thu, 28 May 2015 15:32:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James Nunez (james.a.nunez@intel.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/15015&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/15015&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6194&quot; title=&quot;Interop 2.5.3&amp;lt;-&amp;gt;2.7 sanity test_162c: Value too large for defined data type&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6194&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6194&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: Skip sanity 162c for MDS older than 2.6.92&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 388a15a39184ac80e94b978932e9e3fd88268b19&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="116677" author="jamesanunez" created="Thu, 28 May 2015 14:13:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4239&quot; title=&quot;lfs fid2path ioctl err -75: Value too large for defined data type (75)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4239&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4239&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with commit 825570b0b03e0fd70a removed the limit of a path with 100 subdirectories or more and added sanity test 162c to test this. This patch was added in Lustre 2.7.0 in tag 2.6.92. The test needs a check the server version before running. If the server is 2.6.92 or above, run the test. If not, skip it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll upload a patch for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
